    <pre>This issue should contain the relevant information needed to change the 
documentation.  

It's worth noting that one edit's the blog's css separately, here: 
<a href="https://github.com/openhatch/oh-mainline/blob/master/mysite/static/css/blog-">https://github.com/openhatch/oh-mainline/blob/master/mysite/static/css/blog-</a>
style.css  

The CSS for the rest of the site seems to consist of a small chunk of css in a 
style tag in the html head, and here:
<a href="https://github.com/openhatch/oh-mainline/tree/master/mysite/static/less/base">https://github.com/openhatch/oh-mainline/tree/master/mysite/static/less/base</a>

I'm not too familiar with Less but we can at least link to its documentation in 
our own: <a href="http://lesscss.org/">http://lesscss.org/</a></pre>
